race.comment: ABERLUTELY (5) finished out of the money two starts back then was beaten 2.5 lengths when fourth in a 2000m contest at Pakenham two weeks ago. Has the ability to put the recent run of form behind her in this more suitable contest. PARABELLUM (11) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start when she got a long way back over 1980m at Tatura, beaten 1.5 lengths into fifth. Best figures measure up nicely. DUSTY'S DEEL (4) turned in a better effort to finish second last start, beaten 0.8 lengths over 1800m at Wycheproof. Should enjoy a good run just off the speed. BRASSI ROAD (13) was beaten 7 lengths into sixth in a 2400m contest at Swan Hill last time out. Likely improver with strong top-three prospects. ANCHOR DOWN (1) hasn't lived up to promise shown earlier in his career but hasn't been beaten far his past two, which looks good enough form for this despite the big weight.
